# 2. Mobile App (Expo React Native)

You don't need a published app. You just need a single React Native screen proving your API is mobile-ready. 

## Setup
```bash
npx create-expo-app mobile_app
cd mobile_app
npm install
```

## `mobile_app/App.js`

Replace the default `App.js` with this. It provides a dropdown, a chat window, and hits your local network API.

*(Note: Replace `YOUR_LOCAL_IP` with your desktop's actual local IP address, e.g., `192.168.1.15`, because the mobile simulator cannot resolve `localhost` to your PC).*

```javascript
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { StyleSheet, Text, View, TextInput, Button, ScrollView, SafeAreaView } from 'react-native';
import { Picker } from '@react-native-picker/picker';

// Replace with your computer's local IP address
const API_URL = "http://YOUR_LOCAL_IP:8000/v1/chat";

export default function App() {
  const [tenant, setTenant] = useState('sis');
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
  const [chat, setChat] = useState([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const sendMessage = async () => {
    if (!query) return;
    
    const newChat = [...chat, { role: 'user', text: query }];
    setChat(newChat);
    setQuery('');
    setLoading(true);

    try {
      // For the POC mobile app, we use standard fetch. 
      // In production, we'd use react-native-sse for streaming.
      const response = await fetch(API_URL, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ tenant_id: tenant, query: query })
      });

      const textStream = await response.text();
      
      // Basic parser to extract the streamed tokens into a single string
      const lines = textStream.split('\n');
      let fullText = '';
      
      lines.forEach(line => {
        if (line.startsWith('data: ') && !line.includes('[DONE]')) {
          try {
            const data = JSON.parse(line.substring(6));
            if (data.token) fullText += data.token;
          } catch (e) {}
        }
      });

      setChat([...newChat, { role: 'assistant', text: fullText }]);
    } catch (error) {
      setChat([...newChat, { role: 'assistant', text: "Error connecting to server." }]);
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  return (
    <SafeAreaView style={styles.container}>
      <Text style={styles.header}>AI Copilot Mobile</Text>
      
      <Picker
        selectedValue={tenant}
        style={styles.picker}
        onValueChange={(itemValue) => setTenant(itemValue)}
      >
        <Picker.Item label="Student Info System (SIS)" value="sis" />
        <Picker.Item label="Manufacturing (MFG)" value="mfg" />
      </Picker>

      <ScrollView style={styles.chatArea}>
        {chat.map((msg, index) => (
          <View key={index} style={msg.role === 'user' ? styles.userMsg : styles.botMsg}>
            <Text style={styles.msgText}>{msg.text}</Text>
          </View>
        ))}
        {loading && <Text style={styles.loading}>Assistant is typing...</Text>}
      </ScrollView>

      <View style={styles.inputArea}>
        <TextInput
          style={styles.input}
          value={query}
          onChangeText={setQuery}
          placeholder="Ask a question..."
        />
        <Button title="Send" onPress={sendMessage} />
      </View>
    </SafeAreaView>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { flex: 1, backgroundColor: '#f5f5f5' },
  header: { fontSize: 20, fontWeight: 'bold', textAlign: 'center', margin: 10 },
  picker: { backgroundColor: '#fff', margin: 10 },
  chatArea: { flex: 1, padding: 10 },
  userMsg: { alignSelf: 'flex-end', backgroundColor: '#007AFF', padding: 10, borderRadius: 10, marginVertical: 5, maxWidth: '80%' },
  botMsg: { alignSelf: 'flex-start', backgroundColor: '#E5E5EA', padding: 10, borderRadius: 10, marginVertical: 5, maxWidth: '80%' },
  msgText: { color: '#000' },
  loading: { textAlign: 'center', color: '#888', fontStyle: 'italic' },
  inputArea: { flexDirection: 'row', padding: 10, backgroundColor: '#fff' },
  input: { flex: 1, borderWidth: 1, borderColor: '#ccc', borderRadius: 20, paddingHorizontal: 15, marginRight: 10 }
});
```

### Run it:
